         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Dionysios to Polemon, greeting. Ã– I asked you to pay on behalf of Euterpe daughter of Dionysios, my sister and wife, for the apomoira on the vineyard at Oxyrhyncha, for 1 1/2 metretai at 1500 drachmas, 2250, for expenses 250, total 2500 (dr.), even as I have been irreproachable as regards you; otherwise the plot will be sold. I will send it to you on the 30th. By so doing you will confer on me a kindness. Goodbye. The 35th year, Thoth 21. (Addressed on the verso) To the banker Polemon.</ab>
